<br>
I'm sorry if this is posted somewhere already, but I've not been able to find it if it has (if so - please link the discussion).  I understand the folklore that focus effects on items are more powerful than that same effect created by a mage.  Is this true?  If so, what's the difference?<br>
<br>
For example, a ring with Mana Preservation IV on it supposedly reduces mana used by 10%.  So how much does the norent item that mages summon reduce mana usage?<br>
<br>
The reason I'm asking is, because after I won the Carved Bone Ring off of Terris Thule, I've noticed the change (versus mage item), so was curious how much the difference really was.<br>
<br>
Jwiz<br>
